{"cursor":"3972","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Christian leader\n| type = Bishop name = John Hotham title = Bishop of Ely image = alt = caption =\n| church = Catholic archdiocese = diocese = see = Diocese of Ely term =\n| 1316â1337 predecessor = John Ketton successor = Simon Montacute\n\n| ordination = ordinated_by = consecration = consecrated_by = rank =\n\n| birth_date = birth_place = death_date = about 14 January 1337 death_place =\n| previous_post =\n}}\n\n'John Hotham' (died 1337) was a medieval Chancellor of the Exchequer, Lord High\nTreasurer, Lord Chancellor and Bishop of Ely.\n\nHotham was the son of Alan and Matilda Hotham of Hotham and nephew of William\nHotham, Archbishop of Dublin.\n\nHis early career was in Ireland, where he became Chancellor of the Exchequer of\nIreland until 1310. He was then appointed, on 13 December 1312, Chancellor of\nthe Exchequer in England, a post he held until June 1316.\n\nHotham was elected to Ely about 20 June 1316 and consecrated on 3 October\n1316. Fryde, et al. Handbook of British Chronology p.\n244 Later that year he went to meet the pope in Avignon with the earl of\nPembroke, partly to plead the case for the promotion of Alexander Bicknor as\nArchbishop of Dublin.\n\nAfter returning from Avignon, he was appointed Lord High Treasurer of England\non 27 May 1317 but left that office in June 1318. Fryde,\net al. Handbook of British Chronology p. 104 when he was promoted as\nLord Chancellor of England on 11 June 1318, an office he held until 26\nJanuary 1320. Fryde, et al. Handbook of British\nChronology p. 86\n\nAlthough close to the King Edward II, Hotham switched allegiance to Queen\nIsabella when she successfully invaded to depose the king in September 1326. He\nwas consequently appointed chancellor for the second time by her on behalf of\nthe young Edward III on 28 January 1327. He retired from government in 1328.\n\nHotham died about 14 January 1337 after two years of\nparalysis and was buried in Ely Cathedral.\n","linknr":365,"url":"John_Hotham_(bishop)","recorded":1375075938,"links":["/w/index.php?title=John_Hotham_(bishop)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=John_Hotham_(bishop)&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Bishop_of_Ely","/wiki/Diocese_of_Ely","/wiki/John_Ketton","/wiki/Simon_Montacute","/wiki/Bishop_of_Ely","/wiki/Hotham,_East_Riding_of_Yorkshire","/wiki/William_Houghton_(bishop)","/wiki/Archbishop_of_Dublin","/wiki/Chancellor_of_the_Exchequer_of_Ireland","/wiki/Chancellor_of_the_Exchequer","#cite_note-Handbook244-1","/wiki/Alexander_Bicknor","/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed","/wiki/Lord_High_Treasurer","#cite_note-Handbook104-2","/wiki/Lord_Chancellor","#cite_note-Handbook86-3","/wiki/Edward_II_of_England","/wiki/Edward_III_of_England","#cite_note-Handbook244-1","/w/index.php?title=Ely_Cathedra&action=edit&redlink=1","/w/index.php?title=John_Hotham_(bishop)&action=edit&section=1","#cite_ref-Handbook244_1-0","#cite_ref-Handbook244_1-1","#cite_ref-Handbook104_2-0","#cite_ref-Handbook86_3-0","/w/index.php?title=John_Hotham_(bishop)&action=edit&section=2","/wiki/Oxford_Dictionary_of_National_Biography","/wiki/Oxford_University_Press","/wiki/Digital_object_identifie